einland board member bobby l martin will become nonexecutive chairman of the board mr riddick has  years of business experience including  years leading and managing companies in the steel and building materials industries he was most recently the chief executive officer of jmc steel group inc a leading north american steel pipe and tube manufacturer and was formerly the chief executive officer of formica corporation he has also held roles as president and chief operating officer and chief financial officer of armstrong world industries inc “i am very excited about the opportunity to lead shaleinland working with our talented team i am focused on accelerating operational and growth initiatives so that we can add further value for our customers and capitalize on the opportunities in our core end markets” said mr riddick “i am confident that my experience on the company’s board as well as my work in the steel industry will allow me to hit the ground running and i am looking forward to continuing my work with the board and the entire leadership team” mr riddick continued “i also want to thank rick for his work in positioning shaleinland to meet projected growth in key markets i wish him the best of luck in his future endeavors” about shaleinland shaleinland is a leading specialty industrial distributor of pipe valves fittings and related stainless and aluminum products to the energy food processing transportation and industrial sectors we operate  strategically located branches throughout north america in close proximity to our customers and act as a critical link in our customers’ supply chain we market and sell our products through  distinct and targeted brands for more information visit wwwshaleinlandcom media contact gemma hartblake sonnenshein brunswick group  board committee and charters – world wrestling entertainment inc skip to main content   who we arewhat we doinvestorscommunitycareersnews   wwecom wwe network wwe shop faq contacts who we are company overvie